 commissioned more than 18 years ago are still in use today. Sentek sensors work with extreme accuracy, even under saline conditions (&gt;20dS/m), and across every water content level, from oven dry to saturation. Additionally, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sentektechnologies.com/product-range/soil-data-probes/enviroscan/\">EnviroSCAN</a>&nbsp;probes are fully field serviceable – sensor positions can be adjusted as needed without affecting data integrity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sentek also offers researchers the ultimate in flexibility, making it easy to upscale research products or build upon monitoring systems that are already in place. Those starting with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sentektechnologies.com/product-range/soil-data-probes/diviner-2000/\">Diviner portable monitoring</a>&nbsp;can upgrade to continuous monitoring using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://sentektechnologies.com/product-range/soil-data-probes/enviroscan/\">EnviroSCAN</a>&nbsp;in the same access tubes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Integration is possible with a range of third party data loggers, radio telemetry devices, weather stations, cellular and satellite communication modules and irrigation controllers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For those undertaking projects in plant growth and development, groundwater, soils or water management, Sentek offers a complete range of monitoring and measuring equipment recording at depths from 10 centimetres to 40 metres.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:kadence/column -->\n\n<!-- wp:kadence/column {\"id\":2,\"uniqueID\":\"_8487a7-97\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column inner-column-2 kadence-column_8487a7-97\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\"><!-- wp:kadence/advancedgallery {\"uniqueID\":\"_446e38-5b\",\"columns\":[2,2,2,2,1,1],\"ids\":[20654,20653,20655,20673],\"linkTo\":\"media\",\"showCaption\":true,\"captionStyle\":\"below\",\"captionStyles\":[{\"size