</div></li><li class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item\"><div class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item-inner\"><figure class=\"kb-gallery-figure kb-gallery-item-has-link kadence-blocks-gallery-item-has-caption\"><a href=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Drill-Drop-probe.jpg\" class=\"kb-gallery-item-link\"><div class=\"kb-gal-image-radius\" style=\"max-width:600px\"><div class=\"kb-gallery-image-contain kadence-blocks-gallery-intrinsic\" style=\"padding-bottom:133.33333333333331%\"><img src=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Drill-Drop-probe.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" alt=\"Drill Drop probe\" data-full-image=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Drill-Drop-probe.jpg\" data-light-image=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Drill-Drop-probe.jpg\" data-id=\"20653\" data-link=\"http://localhost/sentek/markets/agriculture/drill-drop-probe/\" class=\"wp-image-20653undefined\"/></div></div><div class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Showing undisturbed installation of the Drill &amp; Drop tapered probe into the soil profile</div></a></figure></div></li><li class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item\"><div class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item-inner\"><figure class=\"kb-gallery-figure kb-gallery-item-has-link kadence-blocks-gallery-item-has-caption\"><a href=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Mr-Peter-Buss.jpg\" class=\"kb-gallery-item-link\"><div class=\"kb-gal-image-radius\" style=\"max-width:683px\"><div class=\"kb-gallery-image-contain kadence-blocks-gallery-intrinsic\" style=\"padding-bottom:149.9267935578331%\"><img src=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Mr-Peter-Buss.jpg\" width=\"683\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Mr Peter Buss\" data-full-image=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Mr-Peter-Buss.jpg\" data-light-image=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Mr-Peter-Buss.jpg\" data-id=\"20655\" data-link=\"http://localhost/sentek/markets/agriculture/mr-peter-buss/\" class=\"wp-image-20655undefined\"/></div></div><div class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Mr Peter Buss, chief scientist Sentek, inspecting an EnviroSCAN probe in a potato field at the end of harvest</div></a></figure></div></li><li class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item\"><div class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item-inner\"><figure class=\"kb-gallery-figure kb-gallery-item-has-link kadence-blocks-gallery-item-has-caption\"><a href=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/field-work.jpg\" class=\"kb-gallery-item-link\"><div class=\"kb-gal-image-radius\" style=\"max-width:800px\"><div class=\"kb-gallery-image-contain kadence-blocks-gallery-intrinsic\" style=\"padding-bottom:75%\"><img src=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/field-work.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" alt=\"field work\" data-full-image=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/field-work.jpg\" data-light-image=\"http://localhost/sentek/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/field-work.jpg\" data-id=\"20652\" data-link=\"http://localhost/sentek/markets/agriculture/field-work/\" class=\"wp-image-20652undefined\"/></div></div><div class=\"kadence-blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Sentek\'s R&amp;D truck, on a mixed cropping farm, checking on field trials.</div></a></figure></div></li></ul></div>\n<!-- /wp:kadence/advancedgallery --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:kadence/column --></div></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:kadence/rowlayout --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->', 'Agriculture', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20101-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-01-28 01:29:06', '2021-01-28 01:29:06', '', 20101, 'http://localhost/sentek/20101-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(20704, 1, '2021-01-28 01:32:38', '2021-01-28 01:32:38', '<!-- wp:kadence/rowlayout {\"uniqueID\":\"_91f145-04\",\"columnGutter\":\"wider\",\"colLayout\":\"left-golden\",\"topPadding\":0,\"bottomPadding\":0,\"firstColumnWidth\":60,\"secondColumnWidth\":40} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-rowlayout alignnone\"><div id=\"kt-layout-id_91f145-04\" class=\"kt-row-layout-inner kt-layout-id_91f145-04\"><div class=\"kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-gutter-wider kt-v-gutter-default kt-row-valign-top kt-row-layout-left-golden kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-m-colapse-left-to-right kt-mobile-layout-row  kt-custom-first-width-60  kt-custom-second-width-40\"><!-- wp:kadence/column {\"uniqueID\":\"_93b885-07\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column inner-column-1 kadence-column_93b885-07\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":24},\"color\":{\"text\":\"#1abc9c\"}}} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color\" style=\"color:#1abc9c;font-size:24px\">When Everything Hinges On Your Data’s Precision, Why Risk It?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With soil moisture sensors able to detect changes in moisture of &gt;0.01 % Volumetric Moisture Content, researchers can understand the soil water uptake patterns of plants and track the movement of water, with precision, through profiles. Data loggers/transmitters can be set to record and upload information at customised time intervals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sentek’s soil moisture probes allow user defined or site specific calibration equations. Researchers can take into account different soil types and produce extremely accurate and valuable data. Sentek offers a proven research solution, rigorously tested and validated by the global scientific community during decades of data collection.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For long-term projects, Sentek can be relied upon to keep measuring as borne out historically since our founding in 1991. Probes commissioned more than 18 years ago are still in use today. Sentek sensors work with extreme accuracy, even under saline conditions (>20dS/m), and across every water content level, from oven dry to saturation. Additionally, the <a href=\"http://localhost/sentek/products/soil-data-probes/enviroscan/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"20246\">EnviroSCAN</a> probes are fully field serviceable – sensor positions can be adjusted as needed without affecting data integrity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sentek also offers researchers the ultimate in flexibility, making it easy to upscale research products or build upon monitoring systems that are already in place. Those starting with <a href=\"http://localhost/sentek/products/soil-data-probes/diviner-2000/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"20253\">Diviner portable monitoring</a> can upgrade to continuous monitoring using <a href=\"http://localhost/sentek/products/soil-data-probes/enviroscan/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"20246\">EnviroSCAN</a> in the same access tubes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Integration is possible with a range of third party data loggers, radio telemetry devices, weather stations, cellular and satellite communication modules and irrigation controllers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For those undertaking projects in plant growth and development, groundwater, soils or water management, Sentek offers a complete range of monitoring and measuring equipment recording at depths from 10 centimetres to 40 metres.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:kadence/column -->\n\n<!-- wp:kadence/column {\"id\":2,\"uniqueID\":\"_8487a7-97\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column inner-column-2 kadence-column_8487a7-97\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\"><!-- wp:kadence/advancedgallery {\"uniqueID\":\"_446e38-5b\",\"columns\":[2,2,2,2,1,1],\"ids\":[20654,20653,20655,20673],\"linkTo\":\"med